[decisions / deviations]
- Modal vs. route: the design called for an open-modal Upload-census flow.
  The existing engine's `open-modal` action dispatches *without* schema-level
  rowData, and `injectRowData` only substitutes `:param` not `{{...}}` in
  endpoints. Substituting `{{policyId}}` into the form runtime via the modal
  path would require either a form-loader query param or extending the
  injectRowData substitutor. Both would expand scope beyond the design.
  Existing convention (add-policy-member-form) uses a sibling route
  `/members/new` to render a server-substituted form. I mirrored that and
  added `/issuance/proposals/[id]/census/new` as the form-render route;
  the census tab's headerAction is now `type: navigate` instead of
  `open-modal`. Logged here because it deviates from the design.
- Files-touched additions beyond design files_touched[]:
  1. src/lib/schemaResolver.ts — added support for `schemas/tables/` and
     `schemas/views/` $ref prefixes. The design references the new
     `tables/census-submission-rows.json` from `views/census-submission-detail.json`
     via `$ref`, but the resolver only handled `schemas/tabs/` and
     `schemas/forms/`. Without this extension the rows table inside the
     detail view would never bundle. Two-line addition mirroring the
     existing tabs branch.
  2. src/components/widgets/forms/formContainer/types.ts — added `accept?`
     to FormFieldConfig (file field's allow-list); widened FormFieldValue
     to include `File | null`. Required to type the new `file` field.
  3. src/components/widgets/forms/formContainer/utils.ts — added a `file`
     branch to buildFieldSchema (Zod refinement that asserts File when
     required) and a `null` default in buildDefaultValues.
  4. src/types/widget.ts — added `uploadField?: string` to the api-mutation
     action variant so the FormContainer two-step submit can pick the
     named file field declaratively.
  5. src/app/issuance/proposals/[id]/census/new/page.tsx — new file (route
     to render the upload form server-side with `{{policyId}}` substituted).
     Sibling to the two files_touched routes; not listed in design but
     forced by the modal→route decision above.

